## Common Failure Modes — Name These if You See Them

- **"Our loop is paid ads → revenue → more paid ads"** — Paid is a *channel*, not a loop, unless your LTV/CAC > 3x and the payback period is < 12 months. Otherwise you're just buying users with a treadmill.
- **"We have 7 loops"** — You have 1, maybe 2 working loops. Naming aspirational ones as "loops" hides the truth. The exercise is to find which one actually compounds.
- **"SEO is our loop"** — SEO is a loop only if user actions produce more indexable surfaces (UGC, reviews, listings). A content team writing posts is a funnel disguised as a loop.
- **"Referrals will save us"** — Referral loops only work if your product already has high satisfaction (Ellis score ≥ 40%). Building a referral program before PMF burns goodwill.
- **"We'll build the loop after we ship the product"** — The loop *is* the product, in a growth sense. If the loop isn't designed in, you're shipping a funnel.

